# Square
  `market_visits++`
  > Brindlewick's market is a ring of dripping awnings, bright apples, wet boots, and sharper eyes.
  > `has_crate` The crate from the cloak seller knocks against your knee with every step.
  + Visit the cloak seller -> [.CloakSeller]
  + Speak to the woman with the blue scarf -> [.BlueScarf]
  + Slip into the alley -> [.Alley]
  + Return to the village inn -> [Village]("/main.saga")

## CloakSeller
  `met_cloak_seller := true`
  ![Cloak Seller]("/assets/images/cloak_seller.png")
  > A narrow man shakes rainwater from a row of heavy cloaks.
  > `has_cloak` He nods approvingly at the cloak you bought from him.
  + `coin >= 2` Buy a dry cloak -> [.BuyCloak]
  + Ask for work -> [.OddJob]
  + Browse and leave -> [Square]

### BuyCloak
  `coin := coin - 2`
  `has_cloak := true`
  > The cloak smells of cedar and sheep oil. It is ugly, warm, and yours.
  -> [..]

### OddJob
  >> [CloakSeller]("/characters.saga") Carry this crate to Mira in the alley. She pays if she likes your face.
  + Take the crate *-> [.TakeCrate]
  + Decline politely -> [..]

#### TakeCrate
  `has_crate := true`
  > The crate clinks with bottles wrapped in straw.
  -> [Square.Alley]

## BlueScarf
  `met_blue_scarf := true`
  ![Blue Scarf]("/assets/images/blue_scarf.png")
  > The woman with the blue scarf watches the crowd reflected in a brass mirror.
  >> `trust_blue_scarf` [BlueScarf]("/characters.saga") You came back. Good.
  + `visited_start` Mention the crescent letter -> [.LetterTalk]
  + Ask about the old watchtower -> [.WatchtowerTalk]
  + Leave her to her mirror -> [Square]

### LetterTalk
  `trust_blue_scarf := true`
  > She folds the mirror shut.
  >> [BlueScarf]("/characters.saga") Then you are already late. Find the archivist's mark beneath the tower.
  + Ask what the mark looks like *-> [..MarkDescription]
  + Return to the market -> [..]

### MarkDescription
  `knows_mark := true`
  >> [BlueScarf]("/characters.saga") A bell inside a closed eye.
  >> If you see it, knock twice and wait.
  -> [..]

### WatchtowerTalk
  >> [BlueScarf]("/characters.saga") The tower was built over a well.
  >> Everything important in Brindlewick is underneath something else.
  + Thank her -> [..]

## Alley
  > The alley behind the market smells of rain, onions, and lamp smoke.
  > `has_crate` Mira's crate grows heavier the longer you carry it.
  + `has_crate` Deliver the crate to Mira -> [.Mira]
  + Visit the locksmith -> [.Locksmith]
  + Return to the cloak seller -> [..CloakSeller]
  + Return to the square -> [Square]

### Mira
  `met_mira := true`
  ![Mira]("/assets/images/mira.png")
  `has_crate := false`
  `coin := coin + 3`
  > Mira counts the bottles and presses three old coins into your hand.
  >> [Mira]("/characters.saga") Counted fair. Tell him I liked your face well enough.
  -> [..]

### Locksmith
  `met_locksmith := true`
  ![Locksmith]("/assets/images/locksmith.png")
  > The locksmith's stall is hardly wider than its door. Keys hang from the ceiling like iron fruit.
  > `lantern_lit` The blue flame in your lantern makes every key cast two shadows.
  + `old_key` Show him the blackened key -> [.BlackKey]
  + `coin >= 1` Buy lamp oil -> [.LampOil]
  + Leave the stall -> [..]

#### BlackKey
  `lower_door_hint := true`
  > He whistles.
  >> [Locksmith]("/characters.saga") That opens a lock that hates daylight. Oil it before you turn it.
  -> [..]

#### LampOil
  `coin := coin - 1`
  `lantern_lit := true`
  > He fills your lantern and lights it with a blue spark from his thumbnail.
  -> [..]
